{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Accurate transcription initiation at protein-coding genes by RNA polymerase II requires the assembly of a multiprotein complex around the mRNA start site. Transcription factor TFIID is one of the general factors involved in this process. Yeast TFIID comprises the TATA binding protein and 14 TBP-associated factors (TAFIIs), nine of which contain histone-fold domains. The C-terminal region of the TFIID-specific yeast TAF4 (yTAF4) containing the HFD shares strong sequence similarity with Drosophila (d)TAF4 and human TAF4. A structure/function analysis of yTAF4 demonstrates that the HFD, a short conserved C-terminal domain (CCTD), and the region separating them are all required for yTAF4 function [[cite:PUB00010434], [cite:PUB00098146]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "2p6v", "name" "Structure of TAFH domain of the human TAF4 subunit of TFIID"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR15138" "TRANSCRIPTION INITIATION FACTOR TFIID SUBUNIT 4"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Transcription initiation factor TFIID component TAF4", "short" "TAF4"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 32, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 1698, "taxa" 6281, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 6126, "sets" 0, "proteins" 6126, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 3882}, "pathways" 31}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR045144", :literature {"PUB00010434" {"URL" nil, "issue" "47", "authors" ["Thuault S" "Gangloff YG" "Kirchner J" "Sanders S" "Werten S" "Romier C" "Weil PA" "Davidson I."], "ISO_journal" "J. Biol. Chem.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1074/jbc.M206556200", "medline_journal" "J Biol Chem", "title" "Functional analysis of the TFIID-specific yeast TAF4 (yTAF(II)48) reveals an unexpected organization of its histone-fold domain.", "year" 2002, "ra